  "body": "#### System information\n\nGeth version: 1.5.0-unstable-89ba380b\nOS & Version: OSX\n#### Expected behaviour\n- estimateGas should return the actual amount of gas used when calling a method. However this is not the case when the method throws an exception\n#### Actual behaviour\n- estimateGas always returns 50000000 units of gas when the method call throws an exception. At a gas price of 20000000000, estimateGas always yields 1 eth, which is unrealistic. One would expect to get the actual gas consumption, which is not zero when the method is called and throws an exception \n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\n- Create a method in a contract that throws. Call estimateGas and evaluate result.\n  Hint: 50000000 seems to be the initialization value for gas-related variables in geth's implementation: https://github.com/ethereum/go-ethereum/blob/master/eth/api.go\n  Seems that the exception throwing interrupts the gas estimation process\n#### Backtrace\n\n```\n[backtrace]\n```\n",
